1. Project Leadership Development Plan (Revised)

Development Goal:

	•	Build leadership skills by taking ownership of data science project components, focusing on leading technical execution and contributing to strategic project outcomes.

Success Measures:

	•	Lead specific aspects of at least two significant data science projects, working collaboratively with the project manager and ensuring successful delivery.
	•	Demonstrate decision-making in key technical areas while coordinating closely with the project management structure.
	•	Receive positive feedback from stakeholders and team members on leadership within the technical components of the projects.

Skill Development:

	•	Develop leadership skills through the management of technical project areas, while supporting overall project goals and working collaboratively with project managers.
	•	Strengthen decision-making abilities in the technical execution of data science initiatives.

Competency Development:

	•	Strategic thinking in aligning technical work with business objectives, supporting the overall project strategy.
	•	Effective communication of technical progress and challenges within the existing project management framework.

Development Timeframe:

	•	Over the next 6-12 months.

Action Plan:

	•	Take ownership of technical components in data science projects, ensuring alignment with the broader project management and business strategy.
	•	Collaborate with the project manager to scope and plan technical work, contributing to the overall project direction without overstepping managerial responsibilities.
	•	Regularly report on technical progress, providing updates to the project manager and stakeholders.
	•	Seek feedback on leadership performance and decision-making within technical aspects of the projects.